dismissalText.commentary: Shubman Gill lbw b Henry 2 (7b 0x4 0x6 13m) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: Huge appeal for lbw as Gill misses an in-dipper and is caught in front of the stumps. The umpire's finger is up in a jiffy. That looks adjacent. Gill has a word with Rohit and reviews. Wow, that looks really close. Was a length ball that tailed back into Gill late. He plays with a straight bat, misses and is rapped on the pad right in front. At worst, it will be umpire's call on leg stump. Nope, replays confirm that the ball would have smashed into the top of leg stump. Gill goes and takes a review with him

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Phillips b Henry 11 (14b 2x4 0x6 18m) SR: 78.57

dismissalComment.html: OH, MY WORD! Phillips, what are you made of! How has he held on to that? Short, wide and Kohli has absolutely smashed that to the right of Phillips at backward point. Any other fielder and that was going for a four. Not when Phillips is around. He leaps, flings out his right hand, and hangs on to an an absolute stunner. The ball was almost behind him, but he catches it while almost being parallel to the ground. WOW! Kohli can't believe it. No one can, really.

dismissalText.commentary: Axar Patel c Williamson b Ravindra 42 (61b 3x4 1x6 84m) SR: 68.85

dismissalComment.html: Top edge, soft dismissal! Axar cannot believe it. Short and spinning in on middle and leg, 93.8kph, he goes back to just direct it to the on side. The bat face was facing down, he never intended to hit it in the air. The ball bounces more, takes the top edge and almost evades Williamson, who runs sideways to his back from short fine leg, sticks out his right hand to hold on to that. Ravindra breaks the 98-run stand

dismissalText.commentary: Hardik Pandya c Ravindra b Henry 45 (45b 4x4 2x6 59m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Skied high and taken in the deep! End of the Hardik show and India lose a massive wicket. Another short ball that is angled in on off and middle, 122.2kph. He swings hard to pull it away but only gets it to deep square leg, where Ravindra momentarily loses it but keeps his composure to catch that safely. Fourth wicket for Henry

dismissalText.commentary: Ravindra Jadeja c Williamson b Henry 16 (20b 1x4 0x6 27m) SR: 80

dismissalComment.html: Williamson does a Phillips at backward point! Jeeeeez! What are these Kiwis? Henry bowls a bouncer outside off, it is the cross-seam delivery. Jadeja delays his shot as he hops and slaps it to the off side. Could have been at least a couple if not for a flying Williamson. New Zealand making fielding at backward point look as easy as ABC!

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammed Shami c Phillips b Henry 5 (8b 0x4 0x6 21m) SR: 62.5

dismissalComment.html: Swings hard, it flies high and Phillips comes running in and takes it. A five-wicket haul for Henry! Another slower one, Shami goes for the big one but only skies it towards deep midwicket. Phillips ain't missing these

dismissalComment.html: Huge appeal for lbw as Gill misses an in-dipper and is caught in front of the stumps. The umpire's finger is up in a jiffy. That looks adjacent. dismissalComment.html: For once, the pull brings about Rohit's undoing. Was a back of a length ball just outside off stump. Rohit looks for a pull, probably the ball didn't arrive as quickly as he was expecting. He gets it right of the cue end of the blade and Young takes a simple enough catch at square leg.

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Phillips b Henry 11 (14b 2x4 0x6 18m) SR: 78.57

dismissalComment.html: OH, MY WORD! Phillips, what are you made of! How has he held on to that? Short, wide and Kohli has absolutely smashed that to the right of Phillips at backward point. Any other fielder and that was going for a four. Not when Phillips is around. He leaps, flings out his right hand, and hangs on to an an absolute stunner. The ball was almost behind him, but he catches it while almost being parallel to the ground. WOW! Kohli can't believe it. No one can, really.

dismissalText.commentary: Daryl Mitchell lbw b Kuldeep Yadav 17 (35b 1x4 0x6 52m) SR: 48.57

dismissalComment.html: Huge appeal for lbw, Gough raises the dreaded finger! Mitchell chats with Williamson and takes it upstairs. Nicely tossed up on a fullish length around off and middle, he comes forward to defend. But the ball spins in past the inside edge to hit him below the knee-roll. Off and half of middle is visible on impact, is the ball doing too much? They wait a bit for longggggg for ball-tracking to build. Three reds and Mitchell is toast! New Zealand lose a wicket and a review, end of a steady partnership
